President Obama has announced his intent to nominate John S. Pistole as the Assistant Secretary for the Department of Homeland Security, specifically for the Transportation Security Administration (TSA). Pistole currently serves as the Deputy Director of the FBI, a position he has held since October 2004. He has more than two decades of service with the FBI, working in various roles within the Counterterrorism Division. Pistole began his career as a Special Agent with the FBI in 1983 and has received several awards for his distinguished service. He is a graduate of Anderson University and the Indiana University School of Law.